90. An adjective is often modified by a partitive genitive ε, 1, 10, 19 superis deorum, equivalent to superis deis in prose. 1, 9. 14 quem fors dieram cumque dabit, equivalent to quemcumque diem. ,

91. In imitation of a Greek construction, a genitive is used modifying a neuter plural adjective: 2, 1, 23 cuncta terrarum, ‘all the world.’
